---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout pageKey="rooftop-solar-varanasi.html" headerVariant="guide">

<section class="py-20">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
<div class="inline-block bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold">Local Solar Guide · Varanasi, Uttar Pradesh</div>
<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold mt-6">Rooftop Solar in Varanasi</h1>
<p class="text-slate-600 text-lg mt-6 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Varanasi homeowners are reducing PUVVNL electricity bills with rooftop solar and PM Surya Ghar subsidies. This guide covers costs, net metering, empanelled installers, and how to get started in Varanasi.</p>
<a href="index.html" class="inline-block mt-8 bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold transition">Check My Solar Savings</a>
</div>
</section>

<section class="pb-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-5">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">DISCOM</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">PUVVNL</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Purvanchal / UPPCL</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Avg Sun Hours</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2">5–5.5 hrs/day</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">Annual average</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Central Subsidy</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">For 3kW · verify at portal</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border"><div class="text-sm text-slate-500">Typical Payback</div><div class="text-xl font-bold mt-2 text-indigo-700">4–6 Years</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-1">After subsidy</div></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Why Rooftop Solar Makes Sense in Varanasi</h2>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Strong Solar Irradiance</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Varanasi receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours per day on average. With consistent sunshine for much of the year and long summer days, rooftop solar performs strongly in Varanasi's climate.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Summer Demand & Solar Peak Align</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Varanasi summers bring intense heat and high air conditioning demand — exactly when solar panels generate most strongly. This alignment means solar delivers maximum financial value during your highest PUVVNL billing months.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Rising PUVVNL Tariffs</h3><p class="text-slate-600">PUVVNL domestic tariffs have risen steadily. Rooftop solar locks in self-generated electricity at zero marginal cost — insulating homeowners from further tariff increases over the system's 25-year lifespan.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-3xl border"><h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">PM Surya Ghar Eligibility</h3><p class="text-slate-600">Varanasi homeowners with a PUVVNL electricity connection are eligible for the PM Surya Ghar Muft Bijli Yojana central subsidy. PUVVNL empanelled installers serve Varanasi and surrounding areas.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">PUVVNL Net Metering in Varanasi</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">How the net metering connection process works for Varanasi homeowners under PUVVNL.</p>
<div class="space-y-4">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">1</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Install via PUVVNL-Empanelled Installer</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Your installer must be empanelled with PUVVNL. Verify on pmsuryaghar.gov.in before signing any contract — non-empanelled installations are not eligible for the central subsidy.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">2</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Submit Net Metering Application to PUVVNL</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">After installation, your installer submits the net metering application to PUVVNL with technical system details. Most empanelled installers manage this on your behalf.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">3</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">PUVVNL Technical Inspection</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">A PUVVNL engineer inspects the installation for grid safety compliance. Typically two to four weeks in Varanasi depending on workload.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">4</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Bi-Directional Meter Installation</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Your existing PUVVNL meter is replaced with a net meter measuring both import and export. A one-time meter replacement fee may apply.</p></div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border flex gap-5 items-start"><div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-700 font-bold flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">5</div><div><h3 class="font-bold mb-1">Commissioning & Net Metering Active</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Once PUVVNL commissions your system, surplus solar exported to the grid earns credits on your monthly electricity bill.</p></div></div>
</div>
<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-6">See our <a href="learn/net-metering-india.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">net metering guide</a> for a full explanation of how bill credits work.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Choosing the Right System Size in Varanasi</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Match your monthly PUVVNL bill to the right system size.</p>
<div class="overflow-x-auto">
<table class="w-full text-sm bg-white rounded-2xl border overflow-hidden">
<thead class="bg-slate-50"><tr><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Monthly PUVVNL Bill</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Recommended Size</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Roof Area</th><th class="text-left p-4 font-semibold">Best For</th></tr></thead>
<tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
<tr><td class="p-4">₹800 – ₹2,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="1kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">1kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">80–120 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Small homes</td></tr>
<tr><td class="p-4">₹1,500 – ₹3,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="2kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">2kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">160–220 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Small families, 2BHK</td></tr>
<tr class="bg-emerald-50"><td class="p-4">₹2,500 – ₹5,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="3kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">3kW System</a> ★ Most popular</td><td class="p-4">240–300 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Medium families, 3BHK</td></tr>
<tr><td class="p-4">₹4,000 – ₹7,000</td><td class="p-4 font-semibold"><a href="5kw-solar-system.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">5kW System</a></td><td class="p-4">400–500 sq ft</td><td class="p-4">Larger homes, heavy AC</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-4">Use our <a href="learn/solar-system-sizing-guide.html" class="text-indigo-600 hover:underline">solar system sizing guide</a> for the full methodology.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-emerald-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">PM Surya Ghar Subsidy in Varanasi</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">Varanasi homeowners with a PUVVNL connection can apply for the central subsidy through pmsuryaghar.gov.in.</p>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Up to 2kW</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">₹30,000/kW</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Central subsidy · verify at portal</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">3kW System Total</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-emerald-700">Up to ₹78,000</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">3rd kW at lower per-kW rate</div></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><div class="text-slate-500 text-sm mb-1">Above 3kW</div><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-700">No central subsidy</div><div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-1">Beyond 3kW capacity</div></div>
</div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-bold mb-3">How to Apply as a Varanasi Homeowner</h3>
<ol class="space-y-2 text-slate-700 text-sm">
<li>1. Register at <strong>pmsuryaghar.gov.in</strong> using your PUVVNL consumer number</li>
<li>2. Select a PUVVNL-empanelled installer from the portal's list</li>
<li>3. Get system installed, net metering connected, PUVVNL commissioning done</li>
<li>4. Complete subsidy disbursement application on the portal</li>
<li>5. Subsidy credited directly to your bank account — typically weeks to months</li>
</ol>
<p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-4">Verify current rates at pmsuryaghar.gov.in before making financial decisions.</p>
</div>
<div class="mt-4"><a href="learn/pm-surya-ghar-guide.html" class="inline-flex items-center text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline text-sm">Read the full PM Surya Ghar guide →</a></div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Varanasi Areas We Serve</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">We help homeowners across Varanasi connect with PUVVNL-empanelled installers in their locality.</p>
<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
{["Sigra", "Lanka", "Assi", "Sarnath", "Varanasi Cantt", "Orderly Bazar", "Bhelupur", "Nadesar", "Shivpur", "Lahurabir", "Kabir Chaura", "BHU Area", "Sonarpura", "Khojwa", "Pandeypur", "Manduadih"].map(area => (
  <span class="px-4 py-2 bg-slate-100 rounded-full text-sm text-slate-700 font-medium">{area}</span>
))}
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions — Varanasi Solar</h2>
<div class="space-y-4">
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Which electricity company handles rooftop solar in Varanasi?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Varanasi falls under <strong>PUVVNL (Purvanchal Vidyut Vitran Nigam Limited)</strong>, a UPPCL subsidiary covering eastern UP. All net metering applications and solar scheme empanelment are processed through PUVVNL.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">How do I apply for net metering with PUVVNL in Varanasi?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">After installation by a PUVVNL-empanelled installer, your installer submits the net metering application to PUVVNL. PUVVNL inspects the system and installs a bi-directional meter. Typically takes two to six weeks.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Is PM Surya Ghar subsidy available in Varanasi?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Yes. Varanasi homeowners with a PUVVNL connection are eligible. Use a PUVVNL-empanelled installer and apply at pmsuryaghar.gov.in. Verify current amounts before applying.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">What solar system size suits most Varanasi homes?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">For typical Varanasi homes with monthly PUVVNL bills of ₹1,500–₹4,500, a 2kW to 3kW on-grid system covers a significant share of electricity needs. Homes with heavy summer AC use often benefit from 3kW to 5kW.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">How much does rooftop solar cost in Varanasi?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Pre-subsidy cost ranges from ₹60,000 to ₹80,000 per kW. After PM Surya Ghar subsidy (up to ₹78,000 for 3kW), net cost is significantly lower. Always compare quotes from at least two PUVVNL-empanelled installers.</p></div>
<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border"><h3 class="font-semibold">Is Varanasi a good location for solar?</h3><p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">Yes. Varanasi receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours daily. Long hot summers mean high solar generation coincides with peak electricity demand — making solar financially effective for most Varanasi homeowners.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-10">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<div class="bg-indigo-50 border border-indigo-100 rounded-2xl p-6">
<p class="text-slate-700 text-sm">Also serving homeowners in <a href="rooftop-solar-prayagraj.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">Prayagraj</a> and <a href="rooftop-solar-pratapgarh.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">Pratapgarh</a> — both under PUVVNL with the same net metering process. <a href="cities.html" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">View all city guides →</a></p>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Helpful Guides for Varanasi Homeowners</h2>
<div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
<a href="learn/pm-surya-ghar-guide.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Subsidies</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">PM Surya Ghar Guide</div></a>
<a href="learn/net-metering-india.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Billing</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">Net Metering Guide</div></a>
<a href="learn/how-to-choose-solar-installer.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Installers</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">How to Choose an Installer</div></a>
<a href="learn/solar-system-sizing-guide.html" class="block bg-white p-5 rounded-2xl border hover:shadow-md transition"><div class="text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-500 uppercase tracking-wide mb-1">Sizing</div><div class="font-semibold text-sm">Solar System Sizing Guide</div></a>
</div>
</div>
</section>

<section class="py-20">
<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
<div class="bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-[2rem] p-10">
<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">See How Much You Can Save in Varanasi</h2>
<p class="text-slate-300 mb-8">Get a personalised solar savings estimate based on your PUVVNL bill — in under 60 seconds.</p>
<a href="index.html" class="inline-block bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 px-8 py-4 rounded-2xl font-bold transition">Calculate My Solar Savings</a>
</div>
</div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
